From add3f3b4518b8ae4ff3f16301f624bad3a3c48d8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Apr 2026 13:33:33 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] usb: gadget: gxp-udc: reset data toggle on endpoint init

Reset the endpoint data toggle to DATA0 whenever an endpoint is
initialized by setting EVDEPCC_DT_RESET in gxp_udc_ep_init().

Per the USB 2.0 specification, data toggles must be reset to DATA0
on bus reset, SET_CONFIGURATION, SET_INTERFACE, and
CLEAR_FEATURE(ENDPOINT_HALT). The driver already handles the
CLEAR_FEATURE case in gxp_udc_ep_set_halt_and_wedge(), but
gxp_udc_ep_init() -- called from both gxp_udc_connect() (EP0 setup)
and gxp_udc_ep_enable() (non-EP0 configuration) -- never reset the
toggle.

Signed-off-by: Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
---
 drivers/usb/gadget/udc/gxp_udc.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/gadget/udc/gxp_udc.c b/drivers/usb/gadget/udc/gxp_udc.c
index 097055a1da8e..7eb54845529f 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/gadget/udc/gxp_udc.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/gadget/udc/gxp_udc.c
@@ -244,7 +244,7 @@ static int gxp_udc_ep_init(struct gxp_udc_ep *ep, int type, int dir_in,
 	if (type == USB_ENDPOINT_XFER_INT || type == USB_ENDPOINT_XFER_ISOC)
 		val |= EVDEPCC_TXN_PER_UFRAME(1);
 
-	val |= EVDEPCC_EPENABLE;
+	val |= EVDEPCC_EPENABLE | EVDEPCC_DT_RESET;
 	writel(val, ep->base + EVDEPCC);
 
 	val = readl(ep->base + EVDEPSTS);
-- 
2.54.0

